  "texts": [
    "At this time, significant performance bottlenecks may be encountered due to time and storage space constraints.",
    "Therefore, to deal with the challenge of large-scale graph data, it becomes crucial to explore more efficient and resource-friendly graph pooling methods.",
    "Node sampling is an effective strategy for constructing a pooled graph by selecting representative nodes from the original graph.",
    "This process is mainly realized by scoring the nodes, where the scoring is usually based on some kind of importance or contribution of the nodes.",
    "Then, based on the top-k strategy, the k nodes with the highest scores are selected as the nodes of the pooled graph, thus preserving the key information of the original graph."
  ],
